IMO a beach house is the perfect example of the importance of choosing durable materials and finishes. After all, no one wants to come to the beach only to have to walk on eggshells to keep from ruining the upholstery or scratching the floors!⁣

Of course, many of us prefer a casual living vibe these days for our everyday homes too, BUT the need for design choices that will allow a laid-back and fuss-free experience is amped up for a vacation house–especially if you’re ever thinking of renting (or lending) it out. 

When designing this beachfront house for our clients, I made sure to include the following for durability and longevity: 

☑️Performance fabrics
☑️Indoor/outdoor rated rugs
☑️Light-hued flooring (disguises sand + scratches)
☑️Corrosion-resistant metal finishes
☑️Easy-to-clean countertops + cabinetry
☑️Simple, unfussy accessories + décor (no precious tchotchkes or dust-catching collections) 

(📸@julialynnphotography; 💐, styling @katemalpeli)

I can’t believe it’s been almost two decades since I designed my Charlotte, NC home.⁣ At the time, my twin boys weren’t yet a twinkle in my eye and I was still a practicing attorney. I had no idea that the experience of thinking through the thousands of decisions–big and small–to create a beautiful, functional home for myself, my husband, and our future family would eventually grow into a new career and a respected design firm with my name on it. 

But back to “it’s been almost two decades,” meaning it’s time for my home to get a major update. 

I’d like to take this opportunity to remind my husband and children that this will NOT be design by committee. I promise you, that never works – your opinion is what matters. Not your mother, your best friend or your sister-from-another-mister.

Sooooo, the first area on our home update list is our backyard. Shown here is (part of) a dream backyard we completed for a client, and it’s convinced me to add to my own list…

☑️ Generous seating
☑️ A firepit
☑️ A welcoming dining area

(📸 @_dpphoto_ ; 🔨 @arcadiahomesinc)

#tracizellerinteriors #charlotteinteriordesigner #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife

Although I always love when we are able to design custom homes for my clients from the ground up, it was a special joy to get to furnish and decorate this beauty for some of our favorite repeat clients (you can see the whole home in the Sept/Oct 2023 issue of @southernhomemag). ⁣
We worked to enhance the charming, thoughtful architecture by @garrettpnelsonstudio with a fresh, modern, personality-filled design that reflects and elevates our clients’ unique style–all while remaining true to the classic, chic aesthetic TZI has been known for since (gasp!) 2005. 

I think we nailed it! More importantly, our clients love, love, love living in their new home!

#tracizellerinteriors #charlotteinteriordesigner #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife

#tracizellerinteriors #charlotteinteriordesigner #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife

If you know me at all, you know I love to travel. ✈️⁣
I’ve been fortunate recently to visit some extra special spots and–as traveling tends to do–I’ve gained so much inspiration for my clients’ projects. Just getting out of my daily point of view and seeing beautiful architecture, art, and furnishings I don’t normally get to see opens my imagination to a wealth of new and different ideas. 

Because I haven’t gotten around to posting much about my recent travels here, I’ve gathered them all together in this month’s TZI newsletter instead.

If you’re not on my email list, pop over to my website to sign up so you can take a peek into where I’ve been and the shenanigans I’ve gotten up to. Let’s be clear, there wasn’t any dancing on tables 💃, though there may have been an almost-headstand (don’t ask, just know it was all in the name of design!). ✨

#tracizellerinteriors #tzi #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife #charlotteinteriordesign

You can see more of the home in the Sept/Oct issue of Southern Home Magazine on stands and online now.

*SNEAK PEEK* Our fabulous clients were THRILLED to have us working together with their builder @arcadiahomesinc right from the start of their project.

From the marble and wood floor we custom designed for the foyer to the beautiful brick we added to the kitchen and dining room ceiling and everything in between, we ensured the design of their new construction custom home was ideally tailored to them and how they live. 

It’s such a privilege for our team to help elevate the results our clients get frm their custom home builds, and we always love working with the amazing team at Arcadia! 🥰

#tracizellerinteriors #tzi #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife #charlotteinteriordesign

Oh my heart, this was the sweetest project for the most adorable little girls, y’all! ⁣
When our client asked us to help create a nursery for her baby girl on the way and at the same time, give big sister’s room a refresh, we were over the moon! 🌙

This client lives in the Castlewood section of Atlanta, but grew up in south Georga, about 30 minutes from where I did. Not only do we both speak Southern but she’s never met a hairbow or a monogram she didn’t love, so I knew we’d get along just fine! 🎀

For the nursery, we reused some of big sister’s pieces. We custom-framed special artwork made by the client’s grandmother to hang over the crib and added a lovely Schumacher wallcovering. The jute rug feels soft to the touch but the color and texture help cut the sweetness of the space. 

For both girls, we had window seats built into the dormers in their rooms so they’ll both be able to play, read, and daydream in their very own cozy spots. 📖🧸

The girls (and their rooms!) couldn’t be more adorable! 

#tracizellerinteriors #tzi #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife #charlotteinteriordesign

social_posts.post_text:
“To see takes time.”⁣
When I first saw this quote as the title of the now-closed Georgia O’Keeffe exhibit at MoMA in NYC, it gave me pause. 

The exhibit (which was fabulous, by the way) featured many of her early works, including charcoal, pencil, and watercolor works on paper, showing the evolution of her art. 

As a designer, her quote resonated with me. It’s hard to express but there are so many layers and levels to design. Paint, fabrics, and furnishings are crucial but they’re also just scratching the surface. 

Now nearly two decades into my design career, I’ve had to handle thousands and thousands of design details I’d never even noticed in homes when I first started as a designer. It’s taken years to see–and to know how best to handle–that level of detail. 

Today, my clients benefit from all of that time behind me. It informs my innovation and my creative vision and allows me to give them spaces designed with a deeper level of detail and quality. There’s just no substitute for it!

PS -- This piece from 1916 is one of my favorites. Do you recognize the subject? You will when you read the title -- "Tent Door at Night." 

#tracizellerinteriors #tzi #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife #charlotteinteriordesign

What does a designer look at when touring an exclusive hotel penthouse in Paris?⁣

I can't speak for anyone else but when on the design tour of the penthouse in Cheval Blanc (designed by one of the 21st century's most prominent architects, Peter Marino), I was under the sink in the primary suite trying to figure out how in the world they hid the plumbing! 

The good news is I think I figured it out! The bad news is no photography is allowed on the tour due to the valuable artwork inside so I can’t show you anything–not even the plumbing–from the actual penthouse. But this video is are actually views from the penthouse looking outside. Still amazing, oui?! 

#tracizellerinteriors #tzi #classicchicinteriors #modernwelllivedlife #charlotteinteriordesign
